Plan: Fix Plane Proxy (Caddy) Crash Loop
The Plane proxy container was crash-looping with Error: adapting config using caddyfile: parsing caddyfile tokens for 'acme_ca': wrong argument count or unexpected line ending after 'acme_ca', at /etc/caddy/Caddyfile:25. Two compounding bugs caused this and a third hid the fix.

Root cause analysis
Caddyfile syntax bug (primary cause) — The image-baked Caddyfile contains acme_ca {$CERT_ACME_CA}. When CERT_ACME_CA is unset/empty, Caddy receives a bare acme_ca directive with no argument and refuses to start. Caddy's env interpolation does not drop the surrounding directive when a variable is empty.
Wrong volume mount target (hid the fix) — docker-compose.yml mounted config to config, but the container reads /etc/caddy/Caddyfile. So even after writing a corrected Caddyfile to the host, the container kept using its broken built-in copy.
Windows bind-mount path quirks — On Windows/Git Bash, relative bind mounts under ${INSTALL_DIR:-./plane} and the empty default for INSTALL_DIR interact badly. A named Docker volume for /data avoids that whole class of issue; the read-only Caddyfile mount stays as a host bind for editability.
Already-applied fixes (verify they are still in place)
variables.env: CERT_ACME_CA= (empty)
Caddyfile: replaced line 25 acme_ca {$CERT_ACME_CA} with bare {$CERT_ACME_CA} so it disappears when empty; minimal site blocks :80 / :443 import the plane_proxy snippet
docker-compose.yml:519-522: proxy volumes: now ./plane/caddy/config:/etc/caddy:ro + named volume plane-caddy-data:/data; volumes: block declares plane-caddy-data
