Decisions
Override the Caddyfile rather than try to coerce the image's built-in one with env-var tricks — the image's acme_ca {$CERT_ACME_CA} is unconditionally broken when the variable is empty.
Named volume for /data, host bind for /etc/caddy — keeps Caddy's certificate/state private to Docker (avoids Windows file-perm issues) while keeping the Caddyfile editable from the workspace.
Read-only mount (:ro) on the config — prevents Caddy from accidentally writing into the source-controlled directory.
Further considerations
Should the proxy ports for SMTP (25/465/587) stay published? They will collide with any host MTA. Recommendation: comment them out unless email-in is actually used. (Option A: keep, Option B: comment, Option C: gate behind an EMAIL_REPLICAS>0 profile)
